{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AjJVAA1d3PGs6hGzJZ7fYH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Several issues to fix:\n\n1. `@vuepoint/core` can't be resolved вҖ” with `moduleResolution: \"bundler\"`, TypeScript looks at the `exports` field which points to `./dist/index.js`. Since we haven't built yet, those don't exist. I need to add a `typesVersions` or use `paths` mapping, or better yet, point to the source directly for development.\n\nThe typical approach in monorepos is to either:\n- Use `paths` in tsconfig to map `@vuepoint/core` to `../core/src/index.ts`\n- Or use conditional exports with a `development` condition\n\n\nI'll go with the `paths` approach since it's simpler and more standard for monorepos.\n\n2. `.vue` file type declarations needed\n3. `process` and `import.meta.env` need types\n\nLet me fix all of these.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1220,"cache_read_input_tokens":96516,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1220},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d4d0f974-b620-4d0c-b2b4-900d9f160396","uuid":"d514e2ed-2b55-4d5f-9d0c-c64d76ad7493"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AjJVAA1d3PGs6hGzJZ7fYH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Several issues to fix. The main one is that `@vuepoint/core` resolves to `dist/` which doesn't exist yet. I need to use `paths` mapping for development, add `.vue` type declarations, and add node types.\n\n`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`\nIn pnpm monorepos with `moduleResolution: \"bundler\"`, TypeScript follows `exports` in `package.json` which points to `dist/`. Since we haven't built, those files don't exist. The standard solution is `tsconfig` `paths` to remap workspace packages to their source during development. Alternatively, you can add a `\"development\"` condition in exports.\n`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`\n\nLet me update the core package.json to include a source-level entry for development, and add paths:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1220,"cache_read_input_tokens":96516,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1220},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d4d0f974-b620-4d0c-b2b4-900d9f160396","uuid":"eb7c10e7-7361-411d-ba51-939dd52925a0"}
