{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012QaxZ6AQ7tiegUaWKqoyWn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’/**\n     2вҶ’ * output.ts\n     3вҶ’ *\n     4вҶ’ * Formats one or more annotations as structured Markdown for paste into\n     5вҶ’ * Claude Code, Cursor, or any AI agent. This is the \"structured output\"\n     6вҶ’ * that makes VuePoint useful вҖ” greppable selectors, real component names,\n     7вҶ’ * and SFC file paths so agents can find the exact code without guessing.\n     8вҶ’ */\n     9вҶ’\n    10вҶ’import type { Annotation, MarkdownOutputOptions } from './types.js'\n    11вҶ’\n    12вҶ’// в”Җв”Җв”Җ Single annotation в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n    13вҶ’\n    14вҶ’export function formatAnnotation(\n    15вҶ’  ann: Annotation,\n    16вҶ’  opts: MarkdownOutputOptions = {}\n    17вҶ’): string {\n    18вҶ’  const lines: string[] = []\n    19вҶ’\n    20вҶ’  // Header\n    21вҶ’  lines.push(`### Annotation [${ann.id.slice(-6)}]`)\n    22вҶ’  lines.push('')\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’  // Element\n    25вҶ’  lines.push(`**Element:** \\`${ann.elementDescription}\\``)\n    26вҶ’  lines.push(`**Selector:** \\`${ann.selector}\\``)\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’  // Vue component chain\n    29вҶ’  if (ann.componentChain.length > 0) {\n    30вҶ’    const chain = ann.componentChain.map((c) => `<${c.name}>`).join(' вҶ’ ')\n    31вҶ’    lines.push(`**Component:** \\`${chain}\\``)\n    32вҶ’\n    33вҶ’    // Most specific component with a file path\n    34вҶ’    const withFile = [...ann.componentChain].reverse().find((c) => c.file)\n    35вҶ’    if (withFile?.file) {\n    36вҶ’      const display = withFile.file.replace(/^.*?src\\//, 'src/')\n    37вҶ’      lines.push(`**SFC Path:** \\`${display}\\``)\n    38вҶ’    }\n    39вҶ’  }\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’  // Pinia stores\n    42вҶ’  if (ann.piniaStores && ann.piniaStores.length > 0) {\n    43вҶ’    lines.push(`**Pinia Stores:** \\`${ann.piniaStores.join('`, `')}\\``)\n    44вҶ’  }\n    45вҶ’\n    46вҶ’  // Route\n    47вҶ’  if (ann.route) {\n    48вҶ’    lines.push(`**Route:** \\`${ann.route}\\``)\n    49вҶ’  }\n    50вҶ’\n    51вҶ’  // Props (opt-in)\n    52вҶ’  if (opts.includeProps) {\n    53вҶ’    const withProps = [...ann.componentChain].reverse().find((c) => c.propKeys?.length)\n    54вҶ’    if (withProps?.propKeys?.length) {\n    55вҶ’      lines.push(`**Props:** \\`${withProps.propKeys.join('`, `')}\\``)\n    56вҶ’    }\n    57вҶ’  }\n    58вҶ’\n    59вҶ’  lines.push('')\n    60вҶ’\n    61вҶ’  // Feedback\n    62вҶ’  lines.push(`**Feedback:** ${ann.feedback}`)\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’  if (ann.expected) {\n    65вҶ’    lines.push('')\n    66вҶ’    lines.push(`**Expected:** ${ann.expected}`)\n    67вҶ’  }\n    68вҶ’\n    69вҶ’  if (ann.actual) {\n    70вҶ’    lines.push(`**Actual:** ${ann.actual}`)\n    71вҶ’  }\n    72вҶ’\n    73вҶ’  // Screenshot (opt-in вҖ” large, only for async review)\n    74вҶ’  if (opts.includeScreenshot && ann.screenshot) {\n    75вҶ’    lines.push('')\n    76вҶ’    lines.push(`**Screenshot:**`)\n    77вҶ’    lines.push(`![annotation](${ann.screenshot})`)\n    78вҶ’  }\n    79вҶ’\n    80вҶ’  return lines.join('\\n')\n    81вҶ’}\n    82вҶ’\n    83вҶ’// в”Җв”Җв”Җ Batch (all annotations in session) в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n    84вҶ’\n    85вҶ’export function formatAnnotationBatch(\n    86вҶ’  annotations: Annotation[],\n    87вҶ’  opts: MarkdownOutputOptions = {}\n    88вҶ’): string {\n    89вҶ’  if (annotations.length === 0) return '<!-- No VuePoint annotations -->'\n    90вҶ’\n    91вҶ’  const pending = annotations.filter((a) => a.status === 'pending')\n    92вҶ’\n    93вҶ’  const lines: string[] = []\n    94вҶ’  lines.push('## VuePoint Annotations')\n    95вҶ’  lines.push('')\n    96вҶ’  lines.push(`> ${pending.length} pending annotation${pending.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`)\n    97вҶ’  lines.push('')\n    98вҶ’\n    99вҶ’  for (const ann of pending) {\n   100вҶ’    lines.push(formatAnnotation(ann, opts))\n   101вҶ’    lines.push('')\n   102вҶ’    lines.push('---')\n   103вҶ’    lines.push('')\n   104вҶ’  }\n   105вҶ’\n   106вҶ’  return lines.join('\\n').trimEnd()\n   107вҶ’}\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’// в”Җв”Җв”Җ ID generation в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n   110вҶ’\n   111вҶ’export function generateId(): string {\n   112вҶ’  const ts = Date.now().toString(36)\n   113вҶ’  const rand = Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 7)\n   114вҶ’  return `ann_${ts}${rand}`\n   115вҶ’}\n   116вҶ’\n   117вҶ’export function now(): string {\n   118вҶ’  return new Date().toISOString()\n   119вҶ’}\n   120вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DUdWYV9MxKSa3zFtgwxb91","session_id":"7d96043a-1b1d-4ffc-939c-f496d628c2d8","uuid":"623a3b20-2d93-4232-a727-5d0a90882424"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DUdWYV9MxKSa3zFtgwxb91","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the relevant files. Let me create a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Summary: VuePoint Component Inspection Architecture\n\nI've successfully found and read all the key files related to Vue component inspection in the VuePoint monorepo. Here's the complete overview:\n\n### Main Files Found\n\n**Core Files:**\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/composables/useVueInspector.ts` - Main component hierarchy walker\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/index.ts` - Vue package barrel exports\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/index.ts` - Core package barrel exports\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/types.ts` - Shared type definitions\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/plugin.ts` - Vue 3 plugin registration\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/composables/useAnnotations.ts` - Annotation state management\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/selector.ts` - CSS selector generation\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/output.ts` - Markdown formatting utilities\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/primevue-filter.ts` - PrimeVue component filtering\n\n### Key Architecture Insights\n\n**How Component Inspection Works (`useVueInspector.ts`):**\n\n1. **Vue Internal Property**: Leverages `__vueParentComponent` - a property Vue 3 attaches to DOM elements in dev builds (same as Vue DevTools uses)\n\n2. **Hierarchy Walking Algorithm**:\n   - Walks up the DOM from the clicked element to find the nearest element with `__vueParentComponent`\n   - Then walks up the Vue instance tree using the `parent` property\n   - Collects component info (name, file path, props) along the way\n   - Returns ordered array from app root вҶ’ leaf component\n\n3. **Component Name Resolution** (priority order):\n   - `__name` - Set by `<script setup>` compiler\n   - `name` - Set via `defineComponent({ name: '...' })`\n   - `__file` - SFC filename as fallback (with path and extension stripped)\n\n4. **Key Functions**:\n   - `getComponentChain(el)` - Resolves full hierarchy for a DOM element\n   - `getPiniaStoreIds(piniaInstance)` - Extracts active Pinia store IDs\n   - `getComponentStores(chain, piniaInstance)` - Gets stores accessed by a component\n\n### Type Definitions (`types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ninterface VueComponentInfo {\n  name: string           // Inferred component name\n  file?: string          // Path relative to project (e.g., src/views/users/UserCard.vue)\n  line?: number          // Line range (best-effort)\n  propKeys?: string[]    // Prop snapshot (keys only, no values)\n}\n```\n\n### Barrel Exports\n\n**`packages/core/src/index.ts`** exports:\n- Types: `VueComponentInfo`, `Annotation`, `AnnotationStatus`, `VuePointOptions`, etc.\n- Functions: `generateSelector()`, `describeElement()`, `formatAnnotation()`, `buildFilter()`\n\n**`packages/vue/src/index.ts`** exports:\n- `VuePoint` plugin + default\n- `useAnnotationsStore` composable + `AnnotationsStore` type\n- `useVueInspector` composable + `UseVueInspectorOptions` type\n\n### Component Filtering System\n\n**`primevue-filter.ts`** maintains:\n- `PRIMEVUE_FILTER` - 30+ internal PrimeVue component names to exclude\n- `VUE_BUILTINS` - 8 Vue framework components (Transition, Teleport, etc.)\n- `buildFilter()` - Builds a Set<string> from user options with sensible defaults\n\nUsers can customize via `filterComponents` option: disable filtering with `false`, or provide custom array.\n\n### Plugin Integration (`plugin.ts`)\n\n1. Guards against production builds (strips `__vueParentComponent` from prod)\n2. Builds filter set from options\n3. Creates isolated toolbar Vue app (prevents VuePoint's own components from appearing in the chain)\n4. Injects annotation store and options via provide/inject\n5. Registers keyboard shortcut listener (default: `ctrl+shift+a`)\n6. Logs initialization with active ports/features\n\n### Annotation Store (`useAnnotations.ts`)\n\nReactive Vue 3 ref-based store (not Pinia) with methods:\n- `create()` - New annotation with auto-generated ID and timestamps\n- `acknowledge()` - Mark as acknowledged\n- `resolve()` - Mark as resolved with summary\n- `dismiss()` - Mark as won't fix with reason\n- `update()` - Generic patch method\n- Computed `pending` - Filter unresolved annotations\n- Readonly `annotations` state\n\n### Selector Generation (`selector.ts`)\n\nGenerates unique, greppable CSS selectors with priority:\n1. Unique ID\n2. Unique data-testid / data-cy attribute\n3. Tag + filtered classes (excludes generated/dynamic classes)\n4. Nth-child fallback\n\nMaximum depth: 8 levels, stops at unique anchors.\n\n### Output Formatting (`output.ts`)\n\nTwo main formatters:\n- `formatAnnotation()` - Single annotation as Markdown with selector, component chain, SFC path, Pinia stores, route, feedback, expected/actual\n- `formatAnnotationBatch()` - All pending annotations formatted with headers and separators\n\nBoth support optional screenshot and prop keys inclusion.\n\nAll files are fully functional and integrated into a cohesive system for inspecting Vue 3 component hierarchies and generating structured feedback for AI agents."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae8adfe95854175a1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45421\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 28044</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d96043a-1b1d-4ffc-939c-f496d628c2d8","uuid":"a22e8c6c-8c8f-412b-bfd1-59ceeeb4a128","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the useVueInspector.ts file in the VuePoint monorepo. Also find any related files that deal with Vue component inspection, hierarchy walking, or __vueParentComponent. Read the full contents of all relevant files. Also read packages/core/src/index.ts and packages/vue/src/index.ts to understand barrel exports. Thoroughness: medium","agentId":"ae8adfe95854175a1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the relevant files. Let me create a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Summary: VuePoint Component Inspection Architecture\n\nI've successfully found and read all the key files related to Vue component inspection in the VuePoint monorepo. Here's the complete overview:\n\n### Main Files Found\n\n**Core Files:**\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/composables/useVueInspector.ts` - Main component hierarchy walker\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/index.ts` - Vue package barrel exports\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/index.ts` - Core package barrel exports\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/types.ts` - Shared type definitions\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/plugin.ts` - Vue 3 plugin registration\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/vue/src/composables/useAnnotations.ts` - Annotation state management\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/selector.ts` - CSS selector generation\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/output.ts` - Markdown formatting utilities\n- `/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/packages/core/src/primevue-filter.ts` - PrimeVue component filtering\n\n### Key Architecture Insights\n\n**How Component Inspection Works (`useVueInspector.ts`):**\n\n1. **Vue Internal Property**: Leverages `__vueParentComponent` - a property Vue 3 attaches to DOM elements in dev builds (same as Vue DevTools uses)\n\n2. **Hierarchy Walking Algorithm**:\n   - Walks up the DOM from the clicked element to find the nearest element with `__vueParentComponent`\n   - Then walks up the Vue instance tree using the `parent` property\n   - Collects component info (name, file path, props) along the way\n   - Returns ordered array from app root вҶ’ leaf component\n\n3. **Component Name Resolution** (priority order):\n   - `__name` - Set by `<script setup>` compiler\n   - `name` - Set via `defineComponent({ name: '...' })`\n   - `__file` - SFC filename as fallback (with path and extension stripped)\n\n4. **Key Functions**:\n   - `getComponentChain(el)` - Resolves full hierarchy for a DOM element\n   - `getPiniaStoreIds(piniaInstance)` - Extracts active Pinia store IDs\n   - `getComponentStores(chain, piniaInstance)` - Gets stores accessed by a component\n\n### Type Definitions (`types.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ninterface VueComponentInfo {\n  name: string           // Inferred component name\n  file?: string          // Path relative to project (e.g., src/views/users/UserCard.vue)\n  line?: number          // Line range (best-effort)\n  propKeys?: string[]    // Prop snapshot (keys only, no values)\n}\n```\n\n### Barrel Exports\n\n**`packages/core/src/index.ts`** exports:\n- Types: `VueComponentInfo`, `Annotation`, `AnnotationStatus`, `VuePointOptions`, etc.\n- Functions: `generateSelector()`, `describeElement()`, `formatAnnotation()`, `buildFilter()`\n\n**`packages/vue/src/index.ts`** exports:\n- `VuePoint` plugin + default\n- `useAnnotationsStore` composable + `AnnotationsStore` type\n- `useVueInspector` composable + `UseVueInspectorOptions` type\n\n### Component Filtering System\n\n**`primevue-filter.ts`** maintains:\n- `PRIMEVUE_FILTER` - 30+ internal PrimeVue component names to exclude\n- `VUE_BUILTINS` - 8 Vue framework components (Transition, Teleport, etc.)\n- `buildFilter()` - Builds a Set<string> from user options with sensible defaults\n\nUsers can customize via `filterComponents` option: disable filtering with `false`, or provide custom array.\n\n### Plugin Integration (`plugin.ts`)\n\n1. Guards against production builds (strips `__vueParentComponent` from prod)\n2. Builds filter set from options\n3. Creates isolated toolbar Vue app (prevents VuePoint's own components from appearing in the chain)\n4. Injects annotation store and options via provide/inject\n5. Registers keyboard shortcut listener (default: `ctrl+shift+a`)\n6. Logs initialization with active ports/features\n\n### Annotation Store (`useAnnotations.ts`)\n\nReactive Vue 3 ref-based store (not Pinia) with methods:\n- `create()` - New annotation with auto-generated ID and timestamps\n- `acknowledge()` - Mark as acknowledged\n- `resolve()` - Mark as resolved with summary\n- `dismiss()` - Mark as won't fix with reason\n- `update()` - Generic patch method\n- Computed `pending` - Filter unresolved annotations\n- Readonly `annotations` state\n\n### Selector Generation (`selector.ts`)\n\nGenerates unique, greppable CSS selectors with priority:\n1. Unique ID\n2. Unique data-testid / data-cy attribute\n3. Tag + filtered classes (excludes generated/dynamic classes)\n4. Nth-child fallback\n\nMaximum depth: 8 levels, stops at unique anchors.\n\n### Output Formatting (`output.ts`)\n\nTwo main formatters:\n- `formatAnnotation()` - Single annotation as Markdown with selector, component chain, SFC path, Pinia stores, route, feedback, expected/actual\n- `formatAnnotationBatch()` - All pending annotations formatted with headers and separators\n\nBoth support optional screenshot and prop keys inclusion.\n\nAll files are fully functional and integrated into a cohesive system for inspecting Vue 3 component hierarchies and generating structured feedback for AI agents."}],"totalDurationMs":28044,"totalTokens":45421,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2687,"cache_read_input_tokens":41291,"output_tokens":1436,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2687,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
