{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DVfHP9nt6dzQa4D6af3jRU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’## Codebase Patterns\n     2вҶ’- Use `tsconfig.base.json` with `paths` for cross-package resolution; per-package tsconfigs extend it\n     3вҶ’- Root `tsconfig.json` with `noEmit` is used for whole-monorepo typecheck (`pnpm typecheck`)\n     4вҶ’- Per-package tsconfigs have `outDir`/`rootDir` for Vite builds but NOT `composite` (avoids needing built output for dev typecheck)\n     5вҶ’- Package names: `@vuepoint/core`, `@vuepoint/vue`, `@vuepoint/bridge`, `@vuepoint/mcp`, `@vuepoint/api`, `@jumpcloud/nuxt-vuepoint`\n     6вҶ’- Source files already use `@vuepoint/core` imports вҖ” no relative cross-package imports\n     7вҶ’- `.vue` files need `env.d.ts` shim for TypeScript (in packages/vue/src/)\n     8вҶ’- Stub components (AnnotationMarker.vue, AnnotationPanel.vue) created for VuePointToolbar imports\n     9вҶ’- `vite` devDep needed in packages/vue for `import.meta.env` types\n    10вҶ’- `@types/node` at root for `process.env` in plugin.ts production guard\n    11вҶ’- Many US stories may already have working implementations from the original 11 source files вҖ” verify before writing new code\n    12вҶ’- Build: `vite-plugin-dts` (with `rollupTypes: true`) for declaration bundling; `@vitejs/plugin-vue` for SFC compilation\n    13вҶ’- Build: `packages/vue/tsconfig.build.json` with empty `paths: {}` prevents DTS from following `@vuepoint/core` source\n    14вҶ’- Build: MCP and API packages are ESM-only (no CJS) since they're Node.js CLI entry points\n    15вҶ’- Build: `exports` field in package.json must list `types` before `import`/`require`\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’---\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’## 2026-03-04 - US-001\n    20вҶ’- Scaffolded pnpm monorepo with 7 packages: core, vue, bridge, mcp, api, nuxt, playground\n    21вҶ’- Moved 11 source files to correct package locations (types/selector/output/filter вҶ’ core, composables/plugin/components вҶ’ vue, server вҶ’ mcp, api вҶ’ api)\n    22вҶ’- Created barrel exports (index.ts) for @vuepoint/core and @vuepoint/vue\n    23вҶ’- Created stub components (AnnotationMarker.vue, AnnotationPanel.vue) to satisfy VuePointToolbar imports\n    24вҶ’- Created env.d.ts for .vue file type declarations\n    25вҶ’- Root tsconfig.json uses paths mapping to source for development typecheck\n    26вҶ’- pnpm install succeeds, `tsc --noEmit` passes across all packages\n    27вҶ’- Files changed: 36 files (new package.json, tsconfig.json, index.ts files + file moves)\n    28вҶ’- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    29вҶ’  - `composite` project references + `--noEmit` don't work well when dist/ doesn't exist yet; use `paths` mapping instead\n    30вҶ’  - The original source files already had correct `@vuepoint/core` imports, so no import rewrites were needed\n    31вҶ’  - VuePointToolbar.vue imports AnnotationMarker.vue and AnnotationPanel.vue which needed stubs\n    32вҶ’  - `process.env.NODE_ENV` in plugin.ts needs `@types/node`, `import.meta.env.PROD` needs `vite` types\n    33вҶ’---\n    34вҶ’\n    35вҶ’## 2026-03-04 - US-002\n    36вҶ’- Created `vite.config.ts` in all 4 publishable packages: core, vue, mcp, api\n    37вҶ’- @vuepoint/core: Vite library mode вҶ’ ESM (`index.js`) + CJS (`index.cjs`) + declarations (`index.d.ts`)\n    38вҶ’- @vuepoint/vue: Vite library mode + `@vitejs/plugin-vue` for SFC compilation вҶ’ ESM + CJS + dts + CSS\n    39вҶ’- @vuepoint/mcp: Vite library mode targeting Node 18 вҶ’ ESM entry point (`server.js`)\n    40вҶ’- @vuepoint/api: Vite library mode targeting Node 18 вҶ’ ESM entry point (`api.js`)\n    41вҶ’- Added `vite-plugin-dts` and `@vitejs/plugin-vue` as root devDeps\n    42вҶ’- Added `vite` devDep to core, mcp, api packages\n    43вҶ’- Created `tsconfig.build.json` for vue package (empty `paths` to avoid DTS rootDir errors)\n    44вҶ’- Fixed `exports` field ordering in core and vue package.json (`types` first)\n    45вҶ’- Updated all build scripts from placeholder `echo` to `vite build`\n    46вҶ’- `pnpm build` succeeds; `pnpm typecheck` passes clean\n    47вҶ’- Files changed: 4 new vite.config.ts, 1 new tsconfig.build.json, 6 modified package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml\n    48вҶ’- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    49вҶ’  - `vite-plugin-dts` follows tsconfig `paths` and will try to generate declarations for cross-package sources вҖ” use a separate `tsconfig.build.json` with empty `paths` to prevent this\n    50вҶ’  - `rollupTypes: true` in vite-plugin-dts produces a single bundled `.d.ts` file (uses @microsoft/api-extractor under the hood)\n    51вҶ’  - MCP and API packages use top-level `await` so must be ESM-only (no CJS output)\n    52вҶ’  - pnpm `-r` automatically handles build order based on workspace dependency topology\n    53вҶ’---\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n    56вҶ’- Verified existing `useVueInspector.ts` implementation meets all acceptance criteria\n    57вҶ’- Component hierarchy walker: walks `__vueParentComponent` up DOM, then Vue instance tree via `parent`\n    58вҶ’- Name resolution: `__name` вҶ’ `name` вҶ’ `filenameToName(__file)` priority chain\n    59вҶ’- SFC path normalization: strips absolute prefix, returns `src/...` relative path\n    60вҶ’- Vue built-ins filtered via `VUE_BUILTINS` set in `primevue-filter.ts`\n    61вҶ’- Chain reversed to root-to-leaf order (`App вҶ’ Page вҶ’ Leaf`)\n    62вҶ’- Typecheck passes clean\n    63вҶ’- Files changed: prd.json (mark passes), progress.md\n    64вҶ’- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    65вҶ’  - US-001 moved all 11 original source files intact вҖ” many stories may already have working implementations that just need verification + typecheck\n    66вҶ’  - `useVueInspector` returns a composable factory pattern: call with options, get back bound functions вҖ” this is the project's preferred Vue composable style\n    67вҶ’  - The `__vueParentComponent` property is only present in Vue 3 dev builds вҖ” production guard in plugin.ts ensures VuePoint is never active in prod\n    68вҶ’---\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n    71вҶ’- Verified existing `selector.ts` implementation meets all acceptance criteria\n    72вҶ’- `generateSelector()`: walks up DOM building unique CSS path, stops at unique anchors (#id, [data-testid])\n    73вҶ’- Priority chain: #id вҶ’ [data-testid/data-cy/data-e2e/aria-label/name/role] вҶ’ tag+classes вҶ’ :nth-child()\n    74вҶ’- MAX_DEPTH = 8, enforced in the walk loop\n    75вҶ’- `describeElement()`: returns human-readable summary (text content, aria-label, input type, img alt)\n    76вҶ’- Both functions already exported from `@vuepoint/core` barrel\n    77вҶ’- Typecheck passes clean\n    78вҶ’- Files changed: prd.json (mark passes), progress.md\n    79вҶ’- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    80вҶ’  - `selector.ts` also filters dynamic classes (Tailwind JIT, CSS modules) via heuristics вҖ” skip classes >30 chars, starting with digit, or looking like hex hashes\n    81вҶ’  - `CSS.escape()` is used for IDs to handle special characters\n    82вҶ’  - Auto-generated IDs (`:r0:` pattern from React/frameworks) are excluded from the ID strategy\n    83вҶ’---\n    84вҶ’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f0808652-e48a-417f-9c20-e2d9d25dbac2","uuid":"4930f573-d617-4867-a2d3-72fa495f81cf","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/juergen/Downloads/VuePoint/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- Use `tsconfig.base.json` with `paths` for cross-package resolution; per-package tsconfigs extend it\n- Root `tsconfig.json` with `noEmit` is used for whole-monorepo typecheck (`pnpm typecheck`)\n- Per-package tsconfigs have `outDir`/`rootDir` for Vite builds but NOT `composite` (avoids needing built output for dev typecheck)\n- Package names: `@vuepoint/core`, `@vuepoint/vue`, `@vuepoint/bridge`, `@vuepoint/mcp`, `@vuepoint/api`, `@jumpcloud/nuxt-vuepoint`\n- Source files already use `@vuepoint/core` imports вҖ” no relative cross-package imports\n- `.vue` files need `env.d.ts` shim for TypeScript (in packages/vue/src/)\n- Stub components (AnnotationMarker.vue, AnnotationPanel.vue) created for VuePointToolbar imports\n- `vite` devDep needed in packages/vue for `import.meta.env` types\n- `@types/node` at root for `process.env` in plugin.ts production guard\n- Many US stories may already have working implementations from the original 11 source files вҖ” verify before writing new code\n- Build: `vite-plugin-dts` (with `rollupTypes: true`) for declaration bundling; `@vitejs/plugin-vue` for SFC compilation\n- Build: `packages/vue/tsconfig.build.json` with empty `paths: {}` prevents DTS from following `@vuepoint/core` source\n- Build: MCP and API packages are ESM-only (no CJS) since they're Node.js CLI entry points\n- Build: `exports` field in package.json must list `types` before `import`/`require`\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-001\n- Scaffolded pnpm monorepo with 7 packages: core, vue, bridge, mcp, api, nuxt, playground\n- Moved 11 source files to correct package locations (types/selector/output/filter вҶ’ core, composables/plugin/components вҶ’ vue, server вҶ’ mcp, api вҶ’ api)\n- Created barrel exports (index.ts) for @vuepoint/core and @vuepoint/vue\n- Created stub components (AnnotationMarker.vue, AnnotationPanel.vue) to satisfy VuePointToolbar imports\n- Created env.d.ts for .vue file type declarations\n- Root tsconfig.json uses paths mapping to source for development typecheck\n- pnpm install succeeds, `tsc --noEmit` passes across all packages\n- Files changed: 36 files (new package.json, tsconfig.json, index.ts files + file moves)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `composite` project references + `--noEmit` don't work well when dist/ doesn't exist yet; use `paths` mapping instead\n  - The original source files already had correct `@vuepoint/core` imports, so no import rewrites were needed\n  - VuePointToolbar.vue imports AnnotationMarker.vue and AnnotationPanel.vue which needed stubs\n  - `process.env.NODE_ENV` in plugin.ts needs `@types/node`, `import.meta.env.PROD` needs `vite` types\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-002\n- Created `vite.config.ts` in all 4 publishable packages: core, vue, mcp, api\n- @vuepoint/core: Vite library mode вҶ’ ESM (`index.js`) + CJS (`index.cjs`) + declarations (`index.d.ts`)\n- @vuepoint/vue: Vite library mode + `@vitejs/plugin-vue` for SFC compilation вҶ’ ESM + CJS + dts + CSS\n- @vuepoint/mcp: Vite library mode targeting Node 18 вҶ’ ESM entry point (`server.js`)\n- @vuepoint/api: Vite library mode targeting Node 18 вҶ’ ESM entry point (`api.js`)\n- Added `vite-plugin-dts` and `@vitejs/plugin-vue` as root devDeps\n- Added `vite` devDep to core, mcp, api packages\n- Created `tsconfig.build.json` for vue package (empty `paths` to avoid DTS rootDir errors)\n- Fixed `exports` field ordering in core and vue package.json (`types` first)\n- Updated all build scripts from placeholder `echo` to `vite build`\n- `pnpm build` succeeds; `pnpm typecheck` passes clean\n- Files changed: 4 new vite.config.ts, 1 new tsconfig.build.json, 6 modified package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `vite-plugin-dts` follows tsconfig `paths` and will try to generate declarations for cross-package sources вҖ” use a separate `tsconfig.build.json` with empty `paths` to prevent this\n  - `rollupTypes: true` in vite-plugin-dts produces a single bundled `.d.ts` file (uses @microsoft/api-extractor under the hood)\n  - MCP and API packages use top-level `await` so must be ESM-only (no CJS output)\n  - pnpm `-r` automatically handles build order based on workspace dependency topology\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-003\n- Verified existing `useVueInspector.ts` implementation meets all acceptance criteria\n- Component hierarchy walker: walks `__vueParentComponent` up DOM, then Vue instance tree via `parent`\n- Name resolution: `__name` вҶ’ `name` вҶ’ `filenameToName(__file)` priority chain\n- SFC path normalization: strips absolute prefix, returns `src/...` relative path\n- Vue built-ins filtered via `VUE_BUILTINS` set in `primevue-filter.ts`\n- Chain reversed to root-to-leaf order (`App вҶ’ Page вҶ’ Leaf`)\n- Typecheck passes clean\n- Files changed: prd.json (mark passes), progress.md\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - US-001 moved all 11 original source files intact вҖ” many stories may already have working implementations that just need verification + typecheck\n  - `useVueInspector` returns a composable factory pattern: call with options, get back bound functions вҖ” this is the project's preferred Vue composable style\n  - The `__vueParentComponent` property is only present in Vue 3 dev builds вҖ” production guard in plugin.ts ensures VuePoint is never active in prod\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-004\n- Verified existing `selector.ts` implementation meets all acceptance criteria\n- `generateSelector()`: walks up DOM building unique CSS path, stops at unique anchors (#id, [data-testid])\n- Priority chain: #id вҶ’ [data-testid/data-cy/data-e2e/aria-label/name/role] вҶ’ tag+classes вҶ’ :nth-child()\n- MAX_DEPTH = 8, enforced in the walk loop\n- `describeElement()`: returns human-readable summary (text content, aria-label, input type, img alt)\n- Both functions already exported from `@vuepoint/core` barrel\n- Typecheck passes clean\n- Files changed: prd.json (mark passes), progress.md\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `selector.ts` also filters dynamic classes (Tailwind JIT, CSS modules) via heuristics вҖ” skip classes >30 chars, starting with digit, or looking like hex hashes\n  - `CSS.escape()` is used for IDs to handle special characters\n  - Auto-generated IDs (`:r0:` pattern from React/frameworks) are excluded from the ID strategy\n---\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
