{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0175ZMgfTimLVRD5JFEsEekN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The existing `primevue-filter.ts` already has a complete implementation. Let me verify it meets all acceptance criteria and run typecheck.\n\n`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`\n- The `buildFilter()` function uses a clever pattern: Vue builtins are **always** included (even with custom lists), but can be completely disabled with `false`. This means `buildFilter(customList)` gives you `VUE_BUILTINS вҲӘ customList`, while `buildFilter(false)` gives you an empty set вҖ” useful for debugging.\n- The `PRIMEVUE_FILTER` array covers PrimeVue's internal abstraction layers (portals, virtual scrollers, focus traps) and icon components, which are the noisiest parts of PrimeVue's component tree.\n`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`\n\nLet me verify: 35 PrimeVue entries in the filter, Vue builtins always filtered, `buildFilter()` handles all three cases, and `VuePointOptions.filterComponents` is typed correctly. All checks out. Let me run typecheck."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3063,"cache_read_input_tokens":57803,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3063},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4714f8d8-a2f7-4536-9854-ee564e020144","uuid":"8ec79cda-3bb7-4273-947c-736d3b3ac016"}
