{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Wh1XATreHixCsiCk4vYjyf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`\nThe AnnotationPanel is a stub component that VuePointToolbar already imports and renders conditionally. The store provides `remove()` for deletion and `annotations` (readonly ref) for the list. The toolbar passes the entire `AnnotationsStore` as the `store` prop. Key design: VuePoint uses `data-vuepoint=\"true\"` on all its DOM to avoid self-annotation, and `vp-` prefixed CSS classes scoped to avoid host app conflicts.\n`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9905,"cache_read_input_tokens":60569,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9905},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5c50a50-0dc2-45b5-b412-2cf67fbbc3db","uuid":"46f7e5d8-9917-46f8-948e-afb3b3f6b686"}
